Step 1: Install Apache
Ensure Apache is installed on your server. Installation steps vary depending on the operating system:

For Ubuntu/Debian:

bash
Copy code
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install apache2
For CentOS/RHEL:

bash
Copy code
sudo yum install httpd
For Fedora:

bash
Copy code
sudo dnf install httpd
Make sure Apache is running:

bash
Copy code
sudo systemctl start httpd # or apache2 depending on your system
sudo systemctl enable httpd # or apache2
Step 2: Install FastAPI and Uvicorn
Set up your Python environment and install FastAPI and Uvicorn:

bash
Copy code
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Use `venv\Scripts\activate` on Windows
pip install fastapi uvicorn
Create your FastAPI application if you haven’t already. Here's a simple example in a file named main.py:

python
Copy code
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/")
async def root():
    return {"message": "Hello World"}
Step 3: Run Uvicorn with FastAPI
Run Uvicorn on a localhost port, let’s say 8000:

uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000


Step 4: Configure Apache to Proxy Requests
Enable Necessary Apache Modules:

Enable modules required for proxy functionality:

sudo a2enmod proxy proxy_http proxy_balancer lbmethod_byrequests
sudo systemctl restart apache2

Configure Virtual Host:
Edit or create a new virtual host configuration for Apache. If using the default site, edit /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf on Debian/Ubuntu or /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf on Red Hat-based systems. Add the following inside the <VirtualHost *:80> block:



<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName yourdomain.com

    ProxyPreserveHost On
    ProxyPass / http://127.0.0.1:8000/
    ProxyPassReverse / http://127.0.0.1:8000/

    ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/error.log
    CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/access.log combined
</VirtualHost>